yes, if an expression is specified in group by clause, then it
must match an exact expression in the select list.
Examples of group by clauses listed below:

> > select a from t group by a;

--- 0 row(s) selected.

> > select a+1 from t group by a+1;

--- 0 row(s) selected.

> > select a+1 from t group by a;

--- 0 row(s) selected.

> > select a+1 aa from t group by aa;

--- 0 row(s) selected.

> > select a from tt group by a+1;

**\* ERROR[4197] This expression cannot be used in the GROUP BY clause.

**\* ERROR[8822] The statement was not prepared.
